I am a resident of 157 East Cottage Street Dorchester, MA 02125 and we were notified last week that the sewers will be getting repairs over the next few week and there are currently “no parking" signs the entire length of the street. I understand that they will need the space to complete said repairs and upgrades. My request is that the workers clearly mark perimeter of the area that they intend to work on in order to free up some parking for the residents. 

We had gas line construction on our street this past summer and Feeney Brothers was extremely courteous by clearly marking the spaces they would be working on the following day. They also had a police detail to help direct vehicles as it can be extremely dangerous maneuvering around the large construction equipment obstructing the flow of traffic.
